      "name": "Supply Chain Attack: Malicious npm Package Steals Credentials from Developers",
      "description": "Cisco Talos researchers have identified a malicious npm package that has been downloaded over 50,000 times in the last three weeks. The package, named 'node-utils-plus', mimics the legitimate 'node-utils' library and includes a hidden credential-stealing payload that exfiltrates environment variables, SSH keys, and browser-stored credentials to attacker-controlled infrastructure. The attack exploits the software supply chain, targeting technology companies and individual developers. Once a developer's machine is compromised, the malware attempts lateral movement to CI/CD pipelines. The package has since been removed from the npm registry. Developers who installed this package should rotate all credentials immediately.",
